The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the United States government. Some of the key appointments include Thomas E. Ayres as the General Counsel of the Department of the Air Force, Kenneth Steven Barbic as an Assistant Secretary of Agriculture, Francis R. Fannon as an Assistant Secretary of State (Energy Resources), Johnathan Miller as an Assistant Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development, John F. Ring as a Member of the National Labor Relations Board, James N. Stewart as an Assistant Secretary of Defense, Michael Stoker as the Federal Mediation and Conciliation Director, and Jackie Wolcott as the Representative of the United States of America to the International Atomic Energy Agency and the Vienna Office of the United Nations.